The external footer doesn't include the standard share-this-page functionality because there is no
back-end to handle the form. Instead the share link is simply a mail-to Link.

However it looks as if travel.london2012.com includes theming.js which contains a eventHandler/function
which is trying to attach itself to the share-this link in the footer.

We had no idea that the travel site would include this .js file as it's fairly specific to the main www.london2012 site and had therefore were not expecting it to be used (and hence cause this issue).

As the advanced share functionality is not available, this function should be removed from theming.js .

It looks like travel.london2012 has included a local copy of theming.js - we're not sure if anything else
on the page uses the functions in this file. If they do then simply remove the redundant function below.
Otherwise simply remove theming.js completely.

http://travel.london2012.com/SJPWeb/Version/London2012/Scripts/theming.js

Line 116: Comment out the following lines or if nothing else in this file is used removed the file completely

    $('#footer-share-this').click(function(event) {
        event.preventDefault();
        if($('#share-box:visible').length != 0) {
            $('#share-box').animate({'height': '0px', 'top': '0px'}, 100, function() {$(this).hide()});
            $('#Content').animate({'opacity': 1}, 100);
        } else {
            $('#Content').animate({'opacity': .3}, 300);
            $('#share-box').css({'height': '0px', 'top': '0px'}).show().animate({'height': '110px', 'top': '-110px'},300);
        }
    });

